<h2>YouTube WordPress Widget Readme</h2>
<ul>
<li>Author - James Wilson</li>
<li>URL - <a href="http://nothingoutoftheordinary.com/2007/05/31/wordpress-youtube-widget/">http://nothingoutoftheordinary.com/2007/05/31/wordpress-youtube-widget/</a></li>
<li>License - <a href="http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html">GPL</a></li>
</ul>

<h3>Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>WordPress 2.2 or 2.0.x/2.1.x with <a href="http://automattic.com/code/widgets/">WordPress Widgets</a></li>
</ul>

<h3>Installation</h3>
<ol>
<li>Download <a href="http://nothingoutoftheordinary.com/wp-content/uploads/2007/05/youtube.zip">youtube.zip</a> (<a href="http://nothingoutoftheordinary.com/wp-content/uploads/2007/05/youtube.tar.gz">gz</a>)</li>
<li>Extract and upload youtube.php to the plugins/ directory</li>
<li>Enable YouTube Widget in the Plugin admin panel</li>
<li>In widget admin panel, place YouTube in the sidebar, and edit it to enter the YouTube URL, not the embed code</li>
</ol>


